newsitem.title: USA: CME lumber futures close mixed at new highs.
newsitem.headline: CME lumber futures close mixed at new highs.

text.p: CME lumber futures closed mixed with the two nearbys up after posting new contract highs and reaching the highest price level in two years.
September posted a new high of $401.80 and November $367.00 per tbf. Futures ended $4.40 higher to $3.40 lower with September up most at $400.90 and November up $2.80 at $362.50 per tbf.
Much of the strength came from continued strong cash.
"Futures are at a discount and cash showing no signs of breaking," said Neil Schmaedick, Smith Barney Forest Products analyst.
Schmaedick also cited arbitrage trading where wholesalers are selling and then buying futures because of the discount futures hold to cash.
Random Length quoted cash spruce at $414 per tbf, up $2 from midweek and $3 above last Friday's level.
